        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 7:30PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 730 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Wellston, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wellston, Mcarthur, Hamden, Coalton, Byer, and Allensville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
